    "These developments underscore the role of DL in not only streamlining fossil classification but also driving paleontological research toward more data-driven and hypothesis-testing frameworks.",
    "A critical factor contributing to the success of these approaches is the application of data augmentation techniques during preprocessing.",
    "Methods such as random rotations, scaling, and brightness adjustments artificially expand the diversity of training data, addressing the inherent class imbalance in paleontology.",
    "This is especially important given the uneven fossil record, where some fossil types are significantly underrepresented.",
    "Data augmentation has proven to be indispensable in low-data regimes, ensuring that models achieve high accuracy despite the scarcity of labeled samples."
